{
    "id": 20733,
    "title": "Opinion Announcement - June 16, 1997",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 192.782,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 192.782,
                "byte_start": 28672,
                "byte_stop": 799702,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 11.856,
                        "byte_start": 28672,
                        "byte_stop": 76110,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.856,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 76110,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 95-1340, Hughes Aircraft Company against the United States versus ex rel. Schumer will be announced by Justice Thomas."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.856,
                        "stop": 192.782,
                        "byte_start": 76110,
                        "byte_stop": 799702,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.856,
                                "stop": 18.458,
                                "byte_start": 76110,
                                "byte_stop": 102546,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.458,
                                "stop": 32.689,
                                "byte_start": 102546,
                                "byte_stop": 159493,
                                "text": "It arises under the qui tam provision of the False Claims Act which permits private parties to bring an action on behalf of the United States against any person who has submitted a false claim to the Government."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 32.689,
                                "stop": 48.263,
                                "byte_start": 159493,
                                "byte_stop": 221769,
                                "text": "Respondents brought this qui tam action in 1989 alleging that petitioner\u0027s internal cost accounting practices resulted in significant overcharges submitted to the Government between 1982 and 1984."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.263,
                                "stop": 55.506,
                                "byte_start": 221769,
                                "byte_stop": 250713,
                                "text": "Before the lower courts could reach the merits of respondent\u0027s claims, they had to address two jurisdictional issues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.506,
                                "stop": 71.214,
                                "byte_start": 250713,
                                "byte_stop": 313616,
                                "text": "First, whether to apply retroactively in 1986 amendment which expanded qui tam actions to include actions such as this one in situations where the Government already had the information involved."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.214,
                                "stop": 84.74,
                                "byte_start": 313616,
                                "byte_stop": 367637,
                                "text": "And secondly, if so, whether the Government\u0027s disclosure of its audits to petitioner\u0027s employers -- employees barred the actions under the 1986 amendment\u0027s public disclosure bar."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.74,
                                "stop": 104.099,
                                "byte_start": 367637,
                                "byte_stop": 445168,
                                "text": "The Ninth Circuit held that the 1986 amendment applied to this action relying on its reading of our decisions -- our decision three terms ago in Landgraf versus USI Film Products and further held that this action was not barred by that amendment\u0027s public disclosure bar."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 104.099,
                                "stop": 107.708,
                                "byte_start": 445168,
                                "byte_stop": 459588,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk to date, we reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 107.708,
                                "stop": 122.383,
                                "byte_start": 459588,
                                "byte_stop": 518207,
                                "text": "In Landgraf, we reiterated the longstanding presumption that legislation which has a retroactive effect does not apply to pre-enactment conduct unless Congress evidences a clear intent to the contrary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.383,
                                "stop": 129.739,
                                "byte_start": 518207,
                                "byte_stop": 547673,
                                "text": "Nothing in the 1986 amendment even suggests a much less clearly evidence as such an intent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.739,
                                "stop": 135.763,
                                "byte_start": 547673,
                                "byte_stop": 571810,
                                "text": "In the 1986 amendment clearly has a legal effect on pre-enactment conduct."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.763,
                                "stop": 146.66,
                                "byte_start": 571810,
                                "byte_stop": 615382,
                                "text": "It eliminates an absolute defense to a qui tam suit prior disclosure to the Government that was available to qui tam defendants prior to 1986."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.66,
                                "stop": 155.443,
                                "byte_start": 615382,
                                "byte_stop": 650491,
                                "text": "Under our Landgraf presumption, therefore, the amendment does not apply to pre-enactment conduct and this case should have been dismissed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.443,
                                "stop": 161.355,
                                "byte_start": 650491,
                                "byte_stop": 674105,
                                "text": "That -- the 1986 amendment is phrased in jurisdictional terms does not alter our conclusion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.355,
                                "stop": 177.803,
                                "byte_start": 674105,
                                "byte_stop": 739934,
                                "text": "Unlike statues that merely define which court has jurisdiction over a matter, this statute here defines whether jurisdiction will lie in any Court thus speaking not just to the power of the courts, but to the rights and obligations of the parties as well."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.803,
                                "stop": 183.993,
                                "byte_start": 739934,
                                "byte_stop": 764698,
                                "text": "Such statute is as much subject to our presumption against retroactivity as any other."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 183.993,
                                "stop": 190.199,
                                "byte_start": 764698,
                                "byte_stop": 789567,
                                "text": "Because we reverse on the first of the two jurisdictional issues, we do not reach the second issue."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 190.199,
                                "stop": 192.782,
                                "byte_start": 789567,
                                "byte_stop": 799702,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
